            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ola <expan><abbr>Q</abbr><ex>uintus</ex></expan> Lucretius Numerianus IIIIviri <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>i</abbr><ex>ure</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>icundo</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>enatum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>onsuluerunt</ex></expan> Fere</supplied>ntini in curia <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usta</ex></expan> basilicae Bar<lb break="no" n="3"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <abbr>April</abbr> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>cribendo</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>a</abbr><ex>dfuerunt</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>itus</ex></expan> Pompeius Potamon <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ublius</ex></expan> Lu<lb break="no" n="4"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost">Sec</supplied>undus <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> Safinius Regillus <lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost">quod <expan><abbr>A</abbr><ex>ulus</ex></expan> Caeci</supplied>lius Quirinalis <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> nomine <expan><abbr>Sex</abbr><ex>ti</ex></expan> Alli Se<lb break="no" n="6"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost">ads</supplied>istente ipso et libellum desideri sui <lb n="7"/><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">proponente</supplied> <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>erba</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ecit</ex></expan> usum eum et ceterorum civium <lb n="8"/><supplied reason="lost">precibus e</supplied>t reverentia quam memoriae pa<lb break="no" n="9"/><supplied reason="lost">tris habere de</supplied>beat velle pecuniae ab Allio Augus<lb break="no" n="10"/><supplied reason="lost">tale oblatae</supplied> adicere in ius avitarium fundum <lb n="11"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>S<supplied reason="lost"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/></supplied>M cum casa et ta<lb break="no" n="12"/><supplied reason="lost">berna</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Marmorfragment mit einem Beschluß des Stadtrates; es stammt wohl von einer der Nebenseiten einer Statuenbasis für die vom Stadtrat geehrte Person. (A): Zuweisung des Fundortes in falsche Regio Italiae. Z. 1: cognomen [Agric]ola oder [Avi]ola; Z. 4: nomen gentile Lu[cilius] oder Lu[cretius]. A. Caecilius Quirinalis f(ilius) ist mit A. Caecilius A.f. Quirinalis aus CIL VI 1492 identisch. Das Adjektiv avitarius ist sonst nicht belegt.</p>
            </div>
